cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SE 

The paper proposes a novel approach to identify dynamical systems using a new representation based on Tree Adjoining Grammar, which is a formalism developed from linguistic considerations. This approach involves multi-objective optimization and evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves non-linear system identification, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
